---
// Honest placeholder instead of fake logos. The self-aware tone is the point.
// We'd rather read as a real early-stage product than fabricate trust.
---

<section class="border-y border-border/50 bg-muted/20 py-12 lg:py-14">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="reveal flex flex-col items-center gap-3 text-center">
      <p
        class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.18em] text-muted-foreground uppercase"
      >
        Trusted by
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-foreground/80 sm:text-lg">
        Honestly? Nobody yet. You could be the first logo on this row.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        Free while we're in beta. <a
          href="mailto:hello@blindbench.dev"
          class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 decoration-border hover:decoration-foreground"
          >Say hi</a
        > and we'll set you up personally.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
